My code is dependent on time
So look at the time mentioned above the message
I'll move onto desktop and elaborate
you only have to look at the time stamp of the last message before I vote
this way, I can simply first check if a message has the right time stamp before I proceed with an ASV
when a player starts talking, the first message will get a time stamp next to their name - here you see 'Tue 08:00' next to my name
but these last few messages have sent much later
you can check the time stamp simply by hovering your mouse over the place of apparently empty space left of a message
so the last 3 messages were sent at 8:17, the 3 messages before that at 8:16, the 2 messages before that at 8:15
and this message is sent at 8:18

now, the time stamp has a direct correspondence with the way village roles are listed in the How2Play section. So if the role appears first in the list, it corresponds with a timestamp of 1 over the hour: so Beholder would correspond to 10.01, 11.01, 12.01 etc.
Gravedigger corresponds with 2 over the hour: 10.02, 11.02, 12.02, etc
Now, since there are only 19 village roles, this means that I can put all the village roles in the first 20 minutes over the hour. So for example, 10.09/11.09/12.09 corresponds with Zealot.
So after 20 minutes we can start again. So 10.21 will be Beholder (or 11.21, 12.21...), 10.22 will be Gravedigger, etc...
And after 20 minutes we can start again, so also 10.41 is Beholder
so for some hour denoted by XX, the clock is at XX.01 or XX.21 or XX.41, I mean beholder. XX.02/22/42 is Gravedigger. XX.03/23/42 is Graverobber... all the way up until XX.19/39/59 for Zealot.
NOTE: YOU HAVE TO LOOK AT THE TIME STAMP OF MY LAST MESSAGE BEFORE I PLACE A VOTE
